      ' <p align="justify"><span><b>(1) </b>Portable fire extinguishers shall be installed in all <i>buildings</i>, except within <i>dwelling units</i>, in conformance with the provisions of Part 6 of Division B of the Fire Code made under the <i>Fire Protection and Prevention Act, 1997</i>.</span></p> <p align="justify"><span><b>(2) </b>In a Group B, Division 1 <i>major occupancy</i>, portable fire extinguishers are permitted to be located in secure areas, or in lockable cabinets provided,</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(a) identical keys for all cabinets are located at all supervisory or security stations, or</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(b) electrical remote release devices are provided and are connected to an emergency power supply.</span></p> <p align="justify"><span ',
