      ' <p align="justify"><span><b>(1) </b>Except as required for aisles by Article 3.3.2.4., the maximum slope of a ramp shall be,</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(a) 1 in 10 in any <i>assembly</i>, <i>care</i>, <i>care and treatment</i>, <i>detention</i> or <i>residential occupancy</i>,</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(b) 1 in 6 in rooms or <i>floor areas</i> classified as <i>mercantile occupancy</i> or <i>industrial occupancy</i>,</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(c) 1 in 8 in any other <i>floor area</i>, and</span></p> <p align="justify"><span class="c1"><span>Note: On January 1, 2022,</span> Clauses 3.4.6.7.(1)(b) and (c) of Division B of the Regulation are revoked and the following substituted: <span>(See: O. Reg. 88/19, s. 79)</span></span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(b) 1 in 6 in an <i>industrial occupancy</i>,</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(c) 1 in 8 in all other <i>occupancies</i>, and</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(d) 1 in 10 for an exterior ramp.</span></p> <p align="justify"><span ',
