    id: "Division B 3.4.6.12.",
    innerHTML:
      ' <p align="justify"><span><b>(1) </b>Except as permitted by Sentences (2) to (4) and Article 3.4.6.14., every <i>exit</i> door shall,</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(a) open in the direction of <i>exit</i> travel, and</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(b) swing on its vertical axis.</span></p> <p align="justify"><span><b>(2) </b>A door serving a single <i>dwelling unit</i> shall swing on its vertical axis.</span></p> <p align="justify"><span><b>(3) </b>Except in a <i>high hazard industrial occupancy</i>, an <i>exit</i> door need not swing in the direction of <i>exit</i> travel where it serves,</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(a) a room, <i>suite</i> or <i>floor area</i> having an <i>occupant load</i> of not more than 60 persons, or</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(b) as part of a <i>means of egress</i> from more than one <i>floor area</i> and the <i>floor areas</i> so served have a total <i>occupant load</i> of not more than 60 persons.</span></p> <p align="justify"><span><b>(4)</b> <i>Exit</i> doors need not conform to Sentence (1) where they serve,</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(a) <i>storage garages</i> serving not more than one <i>dwelling unit</i>,</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(b) accessory <i>buildings</i> serving not more than one <i>dwelling unit</i>, or</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(c) storage <i>suites</i> not more than 28 m<sup>2</sup> in area that are on the <i>first storey</i> of a warehouse and open directly outdoors at ground level.</span></p> <p align="justify"><span ',
