      ' <p align="justify"><span><b>(1) </b>If a fire escape serves any <i>storey</i> above the second, openings located in a zone described in Sentence (2), including access doorways in the exterior walls of the <i>building</i> to which the fire escape is attached, shall be protected by <i>closures</i> conforming to Subsection 3.1.8.</span></p> <p align="justify"><span><b>(2) </b>The zone referred to in Sentence (1) extends from any balcony, platform or stairway of a fire escape to a distance,</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(a) 3 m horizontally,</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(b) 10 m below, and</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(c) 1 800 mm above.</span></p> <p align="justify"><span ',
