    id: "Division B 4.1.6.12.",
    innerHTML:
      ' <p align="justify"><span><b>(1) </b>For valleys in curved or sloped roofs with a slope Î± &gt;10Â°, in addition to the full and partial load cases defined in Article 4.1.6.3., the non-uniform load Cases II and III described in Sentences (2) and (3) shall be considered to account for sliding, creeping and movement of meltwater.</span></p> <p align="justify"><span><b>(2) </b>For Case II as shown in Figure 4.1.6.12., the accumulation factor, C<sub>a</sub>, shall be calculated as follows:</span></p> <p align="center"><img src="120332_e_html_622ec7a7722d830d.gif" name="30" align="bottom" id="30"></p> <p align="justify"><a name="[4.1.6.]_4.1.6._Loads_Due_to_Snow_and_Ra" id="[4.1.6.]_4.1.6._Loads_Due_to_Snow_and_Ra"></a> <span>where,</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>x&nbsp;= horizontal distance from the bottom of the valley, and</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>b&nbsp;= twice the horizontal distance between the bottom of the valley and the peak of the roof surface under consideration.</span></p> <p align="justify"><span><b>(3) </b>For Case III as shown in Figure 4.1.6.12., C<sub>a</sub> shall be calculated as follows:</span></p> <p align="center"><img src="120332_e_html_84ec796af254ba90.gif" name="31" align="bottom" id="31"></p> <p align="justify"><span>where,</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>x, b&nbsp;= as specified in Sentence (2).</span></p> <p align="center"><span class="c1">Figure 4.1.6.12.<br> Snow Loads in Valleys of Sloped or Curved Roofs<sup>(1),(2)</sup></span></p> <p align="center"><span>Forming Part of Sentences 4.1.6.12.(2) and (3)</span></p> <p align="justify"><img src="120332_e_html_ca4032a6f98275a1.gif" name="32" align="bottom" border="0" id="32"></p> ',
