    innerHTML:
      ' <p align="justify"><span><b>(1) </b><i>Water service pipes</i> and <i>fire service mains</i> shall be certified or conform to the standards for the materials listed in Table 7.2.11.2.</span></p> <p align="center"><span class="c1"><span>Table 7.2.11.2.<br></span> Water Service Pipe and Fire Service Main Materials</span></p> <p align="center"><span>Forming Part of Sentence 7.2.11.2.(1)</span></p> <div style="overflow-x:auto;"> <table style="width:fit-content;"> <col> <col> <col> <col> <tr valign="top"> <td>Item</td> <td>Column 1</span></p> <p><span>Material </td> <td>Column 2</span></p> <p><span>Standard </td> <td>Column 3</span></p> <p><span>Limitations </td> </tr> <tr valign="top"> <td>1.</td> <td>Polyethylene pipe and fittings</td> <td>Certified to Series 160 or a higher series of CSA B137.1, âPolyethylene (PE) Pipe, Tubing and Fittings for Cold Water Pressure Servicesâ</td> <td> <br> </td> </tr> <tr valign="top"> <td>2.</td> <td>Crosslinked polyethylene pressure pipe or tube and fittings</td> <td>Certified to CSA B137.5, âCrosslinked Polyethylene (PEX) Tubing Systems for Pressure Applicationsâ</td> <td> <br> </td> </tr> <tr valign="top"> <td>3.</td> <td>PVC pipe and fittings</td> <td>Certified to CSA B137.3, âRigid Polyvinylchloride (PVC) Pipe and Fittings for Pressure Applicationsâ, or certified to CSA B137.2, âPolyvinylchloride (PVC) Injection-Moulded Gasketed Fittings for Pressure Applicationsâ</td> <td>Pipe and fittings must have a rated working pressure of 1 100 kPa or more</td> </tr> <tr valign="top"> <td>4.</td> <td>CPVC pipe and fittings</td> <td>Certified to CSA B137.6, âChlorinated Polyvinylchloride (CPVC) Pipe, Tubing and Fittings for Hot and Cold Water Distribution Systemsâ</td> <td>The design temperature and pressure shall conform to the requirements of the CSA B137.6, âChlorinated Polyvinylchloride (CPVC) Pipe, Tubing and Fittings for Hot and Cold Water Distribution Systemsâ</td> </tr> <tr valign="top"> <td>5.</td> <td>Cast iron water pipe</td> <td>Conform to ANSI/AWWA C151/A21.51, âDuctile-Iron Pipe, Centrifugally Castâ</td> <td>Pipe shall have a cement-mortar lining conforming to ANSI/AWWA C104/A21.4, âCement-Mortar Lining for Ductile-Iron Pipe and Fittingsâ</td> </tr> <tr valign="top"> <td>6.</td> <td>Iron fittings for cast iron or ductile-iron water pipes</td> <td>Conform to ANSI/AWWA C110/A21.10, âDuctile-Iron and Gray-Iron Fittingsâ</td> <td>Pipe shall have a cement-mortar lining conforming to ANSI/AWWA C104/A21.4, âCement-Mortar Lining for Ductile-Iron Pipe and Fittingsâ</td> </tr> <tr valign="top"> <td>7.</td> <td>Rubber gasket joints for cast iron and ductile-iron water pipes</td> <td>Conform to ANSI/AWWA C111/A21.11, âRubber Gasket Joints for Ductile-Iron Pressure Pipe and Fittingsâ</td> <td> <br> </td> </tr> <tr valign="top"> <td>8.</td> <td>Screwed cast iron water fittings</td> <td>Conform to ASME B16.4, âGray Iron Threaded Fittings: Classes 125 and 250â</td> <td>Screwed cast iron water fittings shall be cement-mortar lined or galvanized</td> </tr> <tr valign="top"> <td>9.</td> <td>Type K soft copper tube</td> <td>Certified to ASTM B88, âSeamless Copper Water Tubeâ</td> <td> <br> </td> </tr> <tr valign="top"> <td>10.</td> <td>Solder-joint fittings for copper water systems</td> <td>Conform to ASME B16.18, âCast Copper Alloy Solder Joint Pressure Fittingsâ, or conform to ASME B16.22, âWrought Copper and Copper Alloy Solder-Joint Pressure Fittingsâ</td> <td>Solder-joint fittings not made by casting or the wrought process shall conform to the applicable requirements of ASME B16.18, âCast Copper Alloy Solder-Joint Pressure Fittingsâ</td> </tr> <tr valign="top"> <td>11.</td> <td>Flared-joint fittings for copper water systems</td> <td>Conform to ASME B16.26, âCast Copper Alloy Fittings for Flared Copper Tubesâ</td> <td>Flared-joint fittings not made by casting shall conform to ASME B16.26, âCast Copper Alloy Fittings for Flared Copper Tubesâ</td> </tr> <tr valign="top"> <td>12.</td> <td>PE/AL/PE pipe and fittings</td> <td>Certified to CSA B137.9, âPolyethylene/Aluminum/ Polyethylene (PE-AL-PE) Composite Pressure-Pipe Systemsâ</td> <td> <br> </td> </tr> <tr valign="top"> <td>13.</td> <td>PEX/AL/PEX pipe and fittings</td> <td>Certified to CSA B137.10, âCrosslinked Polyethylene/ Aluminum/Crosslinked Polyethylene (PEX-AL-PEX) Composite Pressure-Pipe Systemsâ</td> <td> <br> </td> </tr> </table> </div> <p align="justify"><span ',
