      ' <p align="justify"><span><b>(1) </b>No compression fitting connecting to plain end pipe or tube shall be used in a <i>plumbing system</i> unless the pipe or tube and fittings are sufficiently stayed, clamped, anchored or buttressed so as to prevent separation during normal service of the system allowing for surge pressures.</span></p> <p align="justify"><span ',
