      ' <p align="justify"><span><b>(1) </b>Where fire protection and life safety systems, and systems with fire protection and life safety functions, are integrated with each other, the systems shall be tested as a whole in accordance with CAN/ULC-S1001, âIntegrated Systems Testing of Fire Protection and Life Safety Systemsâ, to verify that the systems have been properly integrated.</span></p> <p align="justify"><span><b>(2) </b>Sentence (1) does not apply to a <i>building</i> that contains only <i>dwelling units</i> and has no <i>dwelling unit</i> above another <i>dwelling unit</i>.</span></p> ',
