      ' <p align="justify"><span><b>(1) </b><span>Exterior d</span>ampproofing shall be applied from finished ground level to the top of the exterior of the footing.</span></p> <p align="justify"><span><b>(2)</b> Unless otherwise stated in this Subsection, dampproofing shall be installed in accordance with the manufacturerâs instructions with regard to,</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(a) surface priming,</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(b) conditions during application,</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(c) application quantity and rate, and</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(d) curing times.</span></p> <p align="justify"><span><b>(3)</b> Joints, cracks and penetrations shall be sealed to maintain the continuity of the dampproofing, where the dampproofing material is not capable of bridging such discontinuities.</span></p> <p align="justify"><span ',
