      ' <p align="justify"><span><b>(1) </b>Masonry exterior walls, other than <i>cavity walls</i>, in 1 <i>storey buildings</i> and the top <i>storeys</i> of 2 and 3 <i>storey buildings</i> shall be not less than 140 mm thick provided the walls are not more than 2.8 m high at the eaves and 4.6 m high at the peaks of gable ends.</span></p> <p align="justify"><span><b>(2) </b>The exterior walls of the bottom <i>storeys</i> of 2 <i>storey buildings</i>, and exterior walls of the bottom 2 <i>storeys</i> of 3 <i>storey buildings</i> shall be not less than 190 mm thick.</span></p> <p align="justify"><span><b>(3) </b>In exterior walls composed of more than one wythe, each wythe shall be not less than 90 mm thick.</span></p> <p align="justify"><span ',
