      ' <p align="justify"><span><b>(1) </b>An application for a permit under section 8 of the Act to <i>construct</i> or <i>demolish</i> a <i>building</i> shall be made by,</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(a) the owner of the property on which the proposed <i>construction</i> or <i>demolition</i> is to take place, or</span></p> <p align="justify"><span>(b) the authorized agent of the owner referred to in Clause (a).</span></p> <p align="justify"><span><b>(2) </b>An application referred to in Sentence (1) shall be in a form approved by the <i>Minister</i>.</span></p> <p align="justify"><span><b>(3) </b>In Sentence (1),</span></p> <p align="justify">â<span>ownerâ includes, in respect of the property on which the <i>construction</i> or <i>demolition</i> will take place, the registered owner, a lessee and a mortgagee in possession.</span></p> <p align="justify"><span ',
